-- National Capital Region of India to Raise 5 Billion Rupees Selling Bonds
-- Suprotip Ghosh
-- 2010-07-16T04:28:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-16/national-capital-region-of-india-to-raise-5-billion-rupees-selling-bonds.html

          
          
             National Capital Region Planning
Board hired 10 banks to help it to raise 5 billion rupees ($107
million) from a sale of 10-year bonds, according to two people
familiar with the matter.  
 The New Delhi district planner will market 8.68 percent
notes between July 22 and July 26, said the people, who asked
not to be identified as the transaction is private.  
 CRISIL Ltd. gave the notes its top investment grade rating,
the people said. National Capital and investors will have
options to redeem the securities after seven years, they said.  
